My Childhood 
I was torn between hope
and fear
fear that I knew the truth
that I knew the outcome
that hope was fruitless
I was torn
yet I clung
at times letting hope slip
to my fingertips
almost out of my grasp
but, always
I'd tug and pull
to bring it back
only to be hurt again. 

Midnight Musings by 
Tammi Brown Keech
2023
